  "description": [
    "PEOPLES COLUMN _ STRIKES ANT CRIMINALITY To the Editor of The Evening Journal Wilmington Del t our editorial of last evening en 4tled Arbitration or Anarchy In hlch you quote over a column from Age hits the nail squarely on the head insofar as It analyzes conditions But as for the remedy arbitration If you mean a board appointed by some political functionary to hear both sides of a capital and labor controversy and then decide the Issue it will never work because such boards never de cide a question on its merits tho tcndoncy of a board is to spilt thej difference give each sdo a fifty fifty rut notwithstanding the proper decision would be one giving one r\u00ef m were asked The labor unions have learned how to beat the arbitration game The current miners strike affords a good illustration It is well understood that labor should liquidait the same as business has had to do to bring things down to a new workable basis Business Ilqul dated at a cost to Itself of millions some of the largest corporations of the country were entirely lost to their original owners or stockholders be cause of crushing losses sustained"
